gcommit - Git Commit

USAGE:
    gcommit [-m='message'] [-a] [git-commit-arguments...]

DESCRIPTION:
    Commit changes with optional message. Uses APP_CONTEXT
    environment variable to inject contextual information into commit message.

OPTIONS:
    -m='message'
        Commit message

    -a
        Stage all changes before committing

ARGUMENTS:
    git-commit-arguments
        Any valid git commit arguments

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-install-context=CONTEXT
        Context information to inject into commit message

NOTE:
    Makes use of APP_CONTEXT environment variable for contextual information.

EXAMPLES:
    gcommit -m="Fix bug in parser"
    gcommit -a -m="Add new feature"
    gcommit -m="Update docs" --amend
